question.content: What are the instructional components of explicit strategy instruction?

A strategy is not very useful if learners only use the strategy in the class where they learned it. List 3 things that instructors can do to support learners in generalizing use of the strategy to other classes and settings.(See chapter 3 in Writing Better by Graham and Harris).

According to Janice Dole, which 2 reading comprehension strategies are generally most effective?

a) making predictions
b) summarizing
c) asking questions
d) visualizing

Proficient readers more or less automatically get the gist of what they read, but weak readers often have difficulty figuring out the main ideas even at the paragraph level. In the RAP strategy, the A includes 3 questions to help learners figure out the main idea. What are those 3 questions?

When students practice summarizing, teachers need to give them feedback on whether their summaries are well done, and students should learn to self-evaluate their summaries. What are 3 criteria for an effective summary?
When do students need to use generalizations to form a summary?
In the POW + TREE strategy, what does the TREE stand for, and why is it important?

Self-Regulated Strategy Development is obviously related to the earlier unit on Self-Regulated Learning. Take one concept from that earlier unit and explain how it applies to teaching writing strategies.
